3B%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUdotong%2C%20CTO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2F%3F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFireflies.ai%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20built%20a%20product%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-notetaker-work-meetings-tech-save-time-boost-efficiency-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eautomate%20note-taking%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20online%20meetings%2C%20wrote%20that%20the%20company's%20first%20batch%20of%20customers%20in%202017%20were%20getting%20a%20human-run%20Fred.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20soon%20went%20viral%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20with%20nearly%203%2C000%20reactions%20and%20hundreds%20of%20comments.%20While%20some%20applauded%20the%20founders%20for%20their%20approach%2C%20others%20raised%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFireflies.ai%20is%20now%20valued%20at%20%241%20billion%2C%20largely%20thanks%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20virtual%20meetings%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Ramineni%20and%20Udotong%20came%20up%20with%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20meeting%20notetaker%20AI%2C%20their%20backs%20were%20%26quot%3Bagainst%20the%20wall%2C%26quot%3B%20Ramineni%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20we%20said%2C%20we're%20down%20to%20our%20last%20bit%20of%20money%2C%20let's%20figure%20something%20out%2C%20but%20this%20time%2C%20before%20we%20write%20a%20line%20of%20code%2C%20let's%20make%20sure%20that%20we%20can%20actually%20validate%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ramineni%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20CEO%20of%20Fireflies.ai.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20had%20to%20pay%20rent%2C%20and%20SF%20is%20really%20expensive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERamineni%20was%20living%20off%20savings%20after%20a%20brief%20stint%20with%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20Udotong%20had%20never%20had%20a%20full%20time%20job.%20To%20validate%20their%20idea%2C%20Ramineni%20said%2C%20they%20reached%20out%20to%20some%20friends%20in%20the%20tech%20space%20and%20asked%20them%20if%20they%20would%20be%20willing%20to%20pay%20%24100%20a%20month%20for%20their%20meeting%20notes%20to%20be%20fully%20taken%20care%20of%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERamineni%20said%20that%20he%20told%20those%20friends%20that%20there%20would%20be%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-index-indeed-skills-jobs-change-roles-immune-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehuman%20involvement%20and%20oversight%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20did%20not%20specify%20that%20the%20process%20was%20actually%20entirely%20manual.%20Posing%20as%20an%20AI%20bot%20called%20Fred%2C%20the%20two%20founders%20said%20they%20joined%20meetings%20and%20took%20notes%20by%20hand%2C%20and%20they%20usually%20delivered%20the%20notes%20within%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20just%20enough%20money%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20rent%20where%20Sam%20was%20staying%2C%20and%20we%20found%20incredible%20demand%2C%26quot%3B%20Ramineni%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20an%20AI%20bot%2C%20the%20founders%20are%20humans%20who%20could%20not%20be%20omnipresent%2C%20and%20Ramineni%20said%20it%20took%20about%20a%20hundred%20such%20sessions%20for%20them%20to%20grow%20weary%20of%20back-to-back%20meetings%20and%20feel%20the%20constant%20stress%20about%20being%20double-booked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERamineni%20said%20that%20Fireflies.ai%20had%20not%20approached%20any%20investors%20until%20they%20were%20already%20working%20on%20the%20fully%20automated%20product%2C%20and%20there%20was%20no%20overlap%20between%20investment%20and%20the%20founders%20pretending%20to%20be%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20late%202018%2C%20the%20product%20development%20was%20full%20steam%20ahead%2C%20and%20they%20had%20stopped%20manually%20taking%20notes%20for%20customers.%20Ramineni%20said%20they%20were%20kept%20afloat%20by%20small%20checks%20from%20angel%20investors.%20At%20the%20end%20of%202019%2C%20Fireflies.ai%20was%20able%20to%20beta%20test%20its%20product%20and%20do%20live%20demos%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-wealth-hedge-funds-fundraising-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einstitutional%20investors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20raise%20a%20seed%20fund%20of%20more%20than%20%244%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20told%20them%2C%20actually%2C%20for%20the%20first%20couple%20of%20users%2C%20we%20sat%20down%2C%20took%20notes%20for%20them%2C%20and%20it%20helped%20us%20realize%20and%20understand%20what%20it%20means%20to%20do%20good%20notes%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ramineni%20of%20the%20investors.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20they%20were%20impressed%20with%20how%20we%20validated%20the%20problem%20first%2C%20and%20then%20we%20went%20and%20built%20the%20product.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b9a7cbf1-0497-48f8-bbbf-ae281f534af1%5C%22%3EThe%20'fake%20it%20till%20you%20make%20it'%20approach%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETim%20Weiss%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20and%20entrepreneurship%20at%20Imperial%20College%20London%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Fireflies.ai's%20approach%20sounds%20like%20%26quot%3Bpretotyping%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20a%20very%20common%20but%20%26quot%3Bquestionable%26quot%3B%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBasically%2C%20you%20pretend%20you%20have%20a%20product%20to%20learn%20about%20how%20people%20engage%20with%20it%20before%20you%20build%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Weiss.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20something%20that%20is%20done%20at%20the%20very%20early%20stages%20of%20a%20startup%20to%20validate%20an%20idea%2C%20but%20of%20course%20not%20later%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20Fireflies.ai%20may%20have%20simply%20said%20the%20quiet%20part%20out%20loud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20startup%20may%20have%20skimped%20on%20details%20with%20early%20customers%2C%20but%20it%20did%20not%20approach%20institutional%20investors%20until%20the%20company%20had%20a%20functioning%20product%20to%20show%2C%20the%20founders%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20Werbach%2C%20professor%20of%20legal%20studies%20and%20business%20ethics%20at%20the%20Wharton%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%2C%20despite%20the%20risks%2C%20%26quot%3Bfake%20it%20till%20you%20make%20it%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bhallowed%20element%26quot%3B%20of%20tech%20startup%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20done%20right%2C%20it's%20Steve%20Jobs'%20'reality%20distortion%20field'%20and%20countless%20entrepreneurs%20that%20fudged%20on%20details%20to%20get%20the%20time%20or%20resources%20needed%20to%20make%20those%20claims%20real%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Werbach.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20done%20wrong%2C%20it's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftheranos-founder-elizabeth-holmes-prison-time-shortened-again-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EElizabeth%20Holmes%20going%20to%20jail%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20situations%20are%20in%20the%20middle%2C%26quot%3B%20Werbach%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Breality%20distortion%20field%26quot%3B%20is%20%3Cmark%20data-color%3D%5C%22unset%5C%22%3Ea%20term%20coined%20by%20%3C%2Fmark%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-jobs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cmark%20data-color%3D%5C%22unset%5C%22%3ESteve%20Jobs%3C%2Fmark%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cmark%20data-color%3D%5C%22unset%5C%22%3E%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20Apple%2C%20referring%20to%20his%20ability%20to%20convince%20himself%20and%20others%20that%20seemingly%20impossible%20tasks%20are%20achievable%20through%20the%20force%20of%20will%3C%2Fmark%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BInternet%20History%20Podcast%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20show%20that%20documents%20the%20rise%20of%20technology%20that%20may%20seem%20commonplace%20right%20now%2C%20the%20iPhone%20was%20frequently%20failing%20when%20Jobs%20made%20a%20sleek%20demonstration%20of%20it%20back%20in%202007.%20Engineers%20determined%20a%20specific%20order%20of%20demo%20actions%20for%20Jobs%20to%20perform%20to%20prevent%20the%20phone%20from%20crashing%2C%20and%20hard-coded%20all%20the%20demo%20units%20to%20display%20five%20bars%20of%20cell%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFacebook's%20stand-alone%20personal%20assistant%2C%20called%20%26quot%3BM%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20was%20shut%20down%20in%202018%2C%20was%20also%20powered%20by%20humans%20to%20answer%20the%20most%20complex%20queries%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Verge.%20The%20goal%20was%20that%20those%20humans%20would%20help%20train%20the%20AI.%20The%20product%20never%20made%20it%20past%20its%20private%20beta%20stage%2C%20The%20Verge%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERamineni%20said%20that%20as%20of%20today%2C%20the%20AI%20in%20Fireflies%20has%20done%20over%202%20billion%20meeting%20minutes%20and%20has%20taken%20notes%20for%2020%20million%20people%2C%20which%20would%20be%20about%204%2C000%20years%20of%20meetings%20if%20calculated%20by%20an%20eight-hour%20workday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20fair%20to%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-boom-bubble-power-utilities-forecasting-demand-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eskepticism%20around%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20definitely%20do%20believe%20that%20you%20have%20to%20be%20transparent%20in%20that%20if%20you're%20raising%20funds%2C%20talking%20to%20investors%2C%20building%20the%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ramineni.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20fake%20it%20till%20you%20make%20it%20forever%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20not%20how%20it%20works.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartup-story-fake-it-till-you-make-it-fireflies-ai-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1764070081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6920e96ce1a9cbb014dec737%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartup-story-fake-it-till-you-make-it-fireflies-ai-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Founders%20