times%20the%20rate%20of%20demand%20this%20year%20and%20in%202026.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDemand%2C%20defying%20widespread%20bearish%20sentiment%2C%20has%20consistently%20exceeded%20expectations.%20Yet%20supply%20has%20outpaced%20these%20gains%20by%20more%20than%20twofold%2C%20with%20the%20bulk%20of%20growth%20coming%20from%20the%20Americas%2C%26quot%3B%20JPMorgan%20analyst%20Natasha%20Kaneva%20wrote%20on%20Monday.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20JPMorgan's%20view%2C%20the%20stage%20is%20set%20for%20a%20potential%20decline%20of%20as%20much%20as%2050%25%20in%20oil%20prices%20through%20the%20end%20of%202027%2C%20taking%20Brent%20crude%20down%20to%20the%20low%20%2430s%20per%20barrel%20range%20from%20its%20current%20level%20of%20around%20%2463.50.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaneva%20wrote%20that%20supply%20growth%20will%20primarily%20be%20driven%20by%20non-OPEC%2B%20producers%2C%20of%20which%20the%20US%20is%20one%20of%20the%20biggest.%20This%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20surplus%20that%20the%20analysts%20believe%20will%20continue%20pushing%20prices%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnder%20these%20conditions%2C%20Brent%20prices%20are%20likely%20to%20slip%20below%20%2460%20in%202026%2C%20drop%20into%20the%20low%20%2450s%20by%20the%20final%20quarter%2C%26quot%3B%20Kaneva%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20outlook%20worsens%20in%202027%2C%20as%20mounting%20surpluses%20drive%20Brent%20to%20an%20average%20of%20%2442%2C%20with%20prices%20sliding%20into%20the%20%2430s%20by%20year-end.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20surplus%20in%20this%20case%20is%20expected%20to%20reach%202.8%20million%20barrels%20per%20day%20in%202026%20and%20only%20dip%20to%202.7%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emillion%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20the%20following%20year%2C%20unless%20the%20government%20chooses%20to%20intervene.%20Given%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-energy-dominance-oil-gas-prices-taxes-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epro-oil%20dril