%20many%20workers'%20hopes%20for%20four-day%20weeks%20are%20on%20ice%20%E2%80%94%20for%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20appears%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20pushback%20from%20management%20on%20the%20things%20that%20workers%20were%20gaining%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Juliet%20Schor%2C%20a%20Boston%20College%20economist%20who%20has%20researched%20shorter%20workweeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20idea%20of%20permanent%20three-day%20weekends%20isn't%20dead%2C%20Schor%20and%20other%20backers%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Instead%2C%20thanks%20to%20return-to-office%20orders%20and%20companies'%20relentless%20focus%20on%20AI%2C%20broader%20adoption%20might%20simply%20take%20longer%20than%20advocates%20might%20hope.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d2e41c9c-deee-4335-b824-618ee8e5dee5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThanks%2C%209-9-6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20challenge%2C%20for%20now%2C%20is%20that%20the%20four-day%20talk%20doesn't%20always%20jibe%20with%20narratives%20about%20doubling%20down%20on%20work.%20Some%20leaders%20have%20tired%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-tools-for-humanity-startup-culture-hardcore-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediscussions%20about%20work-life%20balance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20big%20employers%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20have%20been%20calling%20workers%20back%20to%20their%20cubicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20ways%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F996-china-games-designer-jack-forsdike-working-hours-culture-office-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eideas%20like%209-9-6%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20slogging%20from%209%20a.m.%20to%209%20p.m.%2C%20six%20days%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20are%20a%20response%20to%20the%20four-day%20workweek%2C%20Schor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20even%20though%20trials%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkers-try-four-day-workweek-burnout-mental-health-research-productivity-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20UK%20to%20New%20Zealand%3C%2Fa%3E%20run%20by%20Schor%20and%20other%20researchers%20have%20indicated%20that%20spending%20less%20time%20on%20the%20job%20can%20leave%20workers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-day-workweek-evidence-prevent-burnout-productivity-ai-well-being-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehappier%20and%20less%20burned%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20without%20compromising%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20many%20CEOs%20are%20focused%20on%20the%20merits%20of%20RTO%20and%20the%20need%20to%20hustle.%20Some%20of%20that%20sober%20speech%20is%20a%20way%20for%20big%20bosses%20to%20signal%20to%20boards%20and%20investors%20that%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbosses-done-caring-worker-feelings-rto-wfh-cost-cutting-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployees%20will%20work%20harder%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20ever%2C%20said%20Vishal%20Reddy%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20WorkFour%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20advocates%20for%20making%20the%20four-day%2C%2032-hour%20workweek%20the%20standard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPart%20of%20it%2C%20I%20think%2C%20is%20a%20performance%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20CEOs'%20directives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddy%20said%20another%20reason%20there%20is%20less%20buzz%20about%20a%20four-day%20workweek%20is%20that%20the%20idea%20is%20no%20longer%20as%20novel%20as%20it%20was%20in%202020%20and%202021%2C%20when%20some%20employers%2C%20looking%20to%20attract%20and%20retain%20workers%2C%20implemented%20the%20concept.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarrying%20the%20idea%20forward%2C%20he%20said%2C%20will%20likely%20require%20waiting%20for%20the%20market%20to%20change%20and%20for%20workers%20to%20regain%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddy%20said%20that%20he%20sees%20proposed%20legislation%20involving%20four-day%20workweek%20pilots%20in%20New%20York%20and%20Maine%20as%20signs%20that%20supporters%20haven't%20given%20up%20on%20the%20concept.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20still%20a%20number%20of%20examples%20of%20companies%20that%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffour-day-workweek-workers-showed-up-on-weekends-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eadopted%20shorter%20schedules%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20nearly%20all%20cases%2C%20once%20employers%20adopt%20the%20schedule%2C%20they%20don't%20go%20back%2C%20Reddy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d6698949-2c99-44f3-8c44-af6411aa50bd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20impact%20of%20AI%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenges%20to%20adopting%20shorter%20weeks%20aren't%20just%20practical%20considerations%2C%20like%20how%20to%20meet%20customers'%20demands%20that%20someone%20picks%20up%20the%20phone%20on%20a%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20it%20feasible%20for%20employers%20to%20pay%20people%20the%20same%20for%20working%20one%20day%20less%2C%20the%20economy%20would%20have%20to%20really%20take%20off%20%E2%80%94%20growing%20in%20the%20high%20single%20digits%20or%20even%20double%20digits%2C%20said%20Pavel%20Shynkarenko%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Mellow%2C%20a%20contractor-management%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20factor%20that%20could%20help%3A%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20technology%20can%20crank%20up%20workers'%20productivity%20enough%2C%20a%20shorter%20week%20could%20be%20doable%2C%20Shynkarenko%20said.%20Having%20only%20four%20days%20on%20the%20clock%20could%20also%20help%20prevent%20widespread%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-safety-pioneer-predicts-ai-could-cause-99-unemployment-by-2030-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eunemployment%20due%20to%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20spreading%20work%20among%20more%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEssentially%2C%20the%20four-day%20workweek%20would%20serve%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bsafe%20harbor%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20economy%20as%20it%20transitions%20to%20one%20where%20bots%20take%20on%20more%20of%20the%20tasks%20that%20now%20fall%20to%20humans%2C%20Shynkarenko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20he%20said%2C%20AI%20could%20make%20it%20so%20that%20even%20a%20four-day%20workweek%20would%20be%20unnecessary.%20Workweeks%20might%20only%20last%20two%20days%2C%20he%20said.%20Regardless%2C%20any%20departure%20from%20five%20days%20as%20the%20norm%20would%20likely%20take%20years%2C%20Shynkarenko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20AI%20can%20do%20more%20heavy%20lifting%2C%20Shynkarenko%20said%2C%20there%20will%20be%20little%20room%20for%20discussion%20of%20truncated%20weeks%20because%20employers%20will%20face%20too%20much%20cost%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20in%20ultra-competitive%20industries%20like%20tech%2C%20an%20abbreviated%20workweek%20could%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20concession%20to%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchor%2C%20the%20economist%2C%20doesn't%20expect%20that%20employers%20will%20be%20able%20to%20avoid%20the%20issue%20indefinitely%2C%20however.%20That's%20because%20although%20workers'%20stress%20and%20burnout%20rates%20have%20improved%20from%20COVID-19%20crisis%20levels%2C%20progress%20has%20plateaued%2C%20and%20remains%20above%20pre-pandemic%20levels%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20still%20in%20that%20level%20of%20heightened%20stress%2C%26quot%3B%20Schor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fabddc92-b6ee-438d-be25-3d8e70dc8f26%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20four-day%20guilt%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20economic%20growth%20were%20to%20occur%20at%20a%20rapid%20enough%20pace%20to%20allow%20for%20a%20four-day%20workweek%2C%20other%20factors%20might%20still%20arise.%20One%20is%20that%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20employees%20might%20feel%20a%20sense%20of%20shame%20about%20working%20less%2C%20said%20Dale%20Whelehan%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20in%20systems%20psychology%20at%20Trinity%20College%20Dublin%2C%20who%20supports%20shorter%20workweeks.%20Until%20January%2C%20he%20served%20as%20CEO%20of%204%20Day%20Week%20Global%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20advocat